  "texts": [
    "The dataset includes a variety of prompts that cover critical risks, adversarial jailbreaks, and cultural contexts, with responses generated by unaligned LLMs.",
    "Annotations are performed at the dialogue level, with prompt and response labels extracted using weak supervision from a jury of LLMs, aligned with human judgments.",
    "Models fine-tuned on AEGIS2.0 demonstrate performance comparable to recent models like WILDGUARD (Han et al., 2024) that have been trained on larger datasets that leverage powerful, non-commercial sources like GPT4.",
    "Our key contributions are as follows:",
    "• We define an extensive and scalable content safety risk taxonomy that identifies 12 core categories and an additional 9 fine-grained risks."
  ],
